AUTOM\u00d3VIL EN MOVIMIENTO\n\nDos violentas explosiones en el puerto de Beirut provocaron este martes al menos 27 muertos y 2.500 heridos en lo que el ministro de Salud consider\u00f3 como \"una cat\u00e1strofe en todos los sentidos\".\n\nEl titular de Salud, Hamad Hassan, asegur\u00f3 que se tratan de \"estimaciones preliminares\".\n\n\"Es una cat\u00e1strofe en todos los sentidos\", lament\u00f3 al ser interrogado por la televisi\u00f3n cuando visitaba un hospital de la capital. \"Los hospitales de la capital est\u00e1n todos llenos de heridos\", subray\u00f3, antes de pedir que se trasladen a otros heridos a los centros hospitalarios de las afueras de la capital.\n\nAntes, el director general de la Seguridad General, Abas, Ibrahim, hab\u00eda dicho que las explosiones podr\u00edan deberse a \"materiales altamente explosivos confiscados desde hace a\u00f1os\", pero agreg\u00f3 que la investigaci\u00f3n determinar\u00e1 la \"naturaleza exacta del incidente\".\n\nNo obstante, los responsables deber\u00e1n \"rendir cuentas\", dijo por su parte el primer ministro, Hasan Diab.\n\nV\u00eddeos difundidos en las redes sociales mostraron una primera explosi\u00f3n seguida de otra que provoc\u00f3 una gigantesca columna de humo. Las deflagraciones hicieron temblar edificios vecinos y provocaron la rotura de vidrios a varios kil\u00f3metros a la redonda.\n\nEl presidente Michel Aoun convoc\u00f3 una \"reuni\u00f3n urgente\" del Consejo Superior de Defensa y el primer ministro decret\u00f3 un d\u00eda de luto nacional para este mi\u00e9rcoles.\n\n\"Es una cat\u00e1strofe dentro (del puerto). Hay cad\u00e1veres en el piso. Ambulancias se llevan los cuerpos\", dijo a la AFP un soldado en las cercan\u00edas del puerto.\n\nLos medios locales difundieron im\u00e1genes de personas atrapadas en los escombros, algunas cubiertas de sangre.\n\n\"Sent\u00ed como un temblor de tierra y despu\u00e9s una enorme deflagraci\u00f3n y los vidrios se rompieron\", dijo a la AFP una libanesa en el centro de Beirut.\n\nUn buque amarrado en el puerto estaba en llamas, constataron periodistas de la AFP. hab\u00eda veh\u00edculos abandonados con los airbags inflados.\n\nL\u00edbano vive la peor crisis econ\u00f3mica en d\u00e9cadas, marcada por una depreciaci\u00f3n de la moneda sin precedentes, Hepsi teredd\u00fct etmeden kendini \u00f6ne atsa da sadece biri bu zorlu g\u00f6revi \u00fcstlenecektir.\nYavuz, annesinin \u00f6l\u00fcm\u00fcyle ilgili \u00f6\u011frendiklerinin ard\u0131ndan b\u00fcy\u00fck bir y\u0131k\u0131ma u\u011frayacakt\u0131r. Ger\u00e7ekler hakk\u0131nda daha fazla bilgi edinmek i\u00e7in u\u011fra\u015ft\u0131k\u00e7a ili\u015fkileri iyice karma\u015f\u0131k bir hal al\u0131r.\nB\u00fcy\u00fckel\u00e7inin \u00f6l\u00fcm\u00fcnden sonra Derman ve Selim yeni g\u00f6revlendirmeleriyle harekete ge\u00e7erler. Hem \u00fclke s\u0131n\u0131rlar\u0131 i\u00e7inde hem de s\u0131n\u0131r d\u0131\u015f\u0131ndaki birliklerimize y\u00f6nelik yeni eylemler planlamaktad\u0131rlar. Tim bu sald\u0131r\u0131l\u0131lar\u0131 \u00f6nlemek i\u00e7in hayati bir g\u00f6rev al\u0131r. Zamanla yar\u0131\u015fan Tim, Derman ve Selim\u2019in ba\u015far\u0131l\u0131 olmalar\u0131n\u0131 engellemek i\u00e7in var g\u00fc\u00e7leriyle sava\u015f\u0131rlar..\n\nT\u00fcrkiye'de ilk defa Genel Kurmay Ba\u015fkanl\u0131\u011f\u0131 ve Milli Savunma Bakanl\u0131\u011f\u0131 i\u015f birli\u011fi ile ger\u00e7ekle\u015ftirilen 'S\u00d6Z', bir \"\u00d6zel Kuvvet Timi'nin\" hikayesini konu al\u0131yor. \n\u00d6n haz\u0131rl\u0131klar\u0131 1 y\u0131l s\u00fcren ve \u00e7ekimleri yakla\u015f\u0131k 3 ayd\u0131r devam eden 'S\u00d6Z' de k\u0131demli \u00fcste\u011fmen ve tim komutan\u0131 Yavuz rol\u00fcn\u00fc ba\u015far\u0131l\u0131 oyuncu Tolga Sar\u0131ta\u015f canland\u0131r\u0131rken; vatan\u0131 i\u00e7in g\u00f6z\u00fcn\u00fc k\u0131rpmadan \u00f6l\u00fcme y\u00fcr\u00fcyen bu \u00f6zel timin di\u011fer mensuplar\u0131n\u0131, Atakan Arslan, Burak Sevin\u00e7, G\u00f6rkem Sevindik, Mustafa Y\u0131ld\u0131ran, Eren Vurdem, Ayta\u00e7 \u015ea\u015fmaz, Mehmet Ali Karaku\u015f, Do\u011fukan Polat, Volkan Uygun, Oktay Samurka\u015f canland\u0131r\u0131yor.\n\nYap\u0131m: Tims&B Productions\nY\u00f6netmen: Ya\u011f\u0131z Alp Akayd\u0131n\nYap\u0131mc\u0131: Anthony Rahayel\nhttps://youtu.be/bcj2J1j3zwg\n.\n\u201cLebnen A7la Balad Bel 3alam\u201d and I\u2019ve been trying to prove it since 2012. I\u2019m Anthony Rahayel, passionate Lebanese, dental surgeon by profession, professional photographer, advocate of great food, blogger, YouTuber, influencer, marketing expert and TV presenter; having one and single aim, that is to show Lebanese and the world, \u201cLebanon as not seen on TV\u201d. I have founded Lebanon\u2019s street food market \u201cSouk el Akel\u201d and won the award of \u201cWorld Street Food Blogger of 2019\u201d.\n\nSince 2012 I\u2019ve had only one goal \u2013 To uncover the real face of Lebanon, not the one that makes headlines on international television shows, but the real, the amazing, traditional and authentic Lebanon. It is that Lebanon I seek to broadcast far and wide. A Lebanon full of life, passion, and vitality, full of people who are producing the most wonderful dishes, meals, desserts, and much, much more.\n\nNoGarlicNoOnions with its food blog (5,000 articles to date), Youtube channel (180,000 subscribers), Instagram account (180,000 followers), google maps (600 million views) and Facebook page (97,000 followers) aims to discover the heroes behind this marvelous country, spread happiness and revive \u201cParis of the Middle East\u201d.\n\nWith every day that goes by and every discovery made and every new venture developed, the aim is one. My aim is to keep people connected to each other and to their roots, to make everyone enjoy, smile when they taste something good and unique, to discover the endless food artisans available across the country... creating a positive and rich environment that allows us all to embrace what we have and embrace life.\n.\n\nOur Projects:\n- The Blog: http://www.NoGarlicNoOnions.com\n- The TV show: We are back to explore MANY of Turkey\u2019s food cities, so you are not going to want to miss an episode. We are starting in Istanbul, and exploring the Turkish street food of Emin\u00f6n\u00fc. We start the day with delicious D\u00d6NER KEBAB, a walk around the Suleymaniye Mosque for 360 views of the Bosphorus. Nearby the mosque, there is an old shop that serves traditional white beans (KURU FASULYE) with PILAV (Turkish rice).  Next, we walk through the Egyptian Bazaar (Spice Market) and stop for pomegranate juice, which is in season right now in Turkey. We also tried a traditional winter drink called BOZA, which is a fermented grain drink. We stop at the Bozdo\u011fan Kemeri and had a \u00c7AY under one of its arches. For dinner, we ate BURYAN KEBAB (pit roast lamb) in an ancient restaurant that maintains traditional recipes.  \n\nThank you to JETFI for keeping us connected around the world while traveling. \nPurchase yours today on Amazon: https://www.amazon.com/dp/B08HN54SV2?ref=myi_title_dp\nFor outside of USA delivery email: amandawang@jetfi-tech.com.\nRental in Taiwan: https://dl.gl/9Km6EBgvE \n\nWe are so excited to be back in Turkey! It\u2019s not just a group of young idealists pushing for the stars.The revolution that has filled Lebanon\u2019s streets for months on end has broad-based support.\n\nYoung and old, rich and poor, Muslim, Christian and Druze are united in their desire to overthrow their corrupt and incompetent leaders and save their country and themselves from economic collapse.\n\nAfter decades of neglect, the country is on its knees. There\u2019s hyperinflation, currency collapse, high unemployment, constant power cuts and people going hungry like never before. And now the country is dealing with the new coronavirus.\n\nIn a rollercoaster ride, Beirut-based correspondent Adam Harvey lived through months of protest and weeks of lockdown and has documented it for Foreign Correspondent.\n\nAdam meets ordinary and extraordinary Lebanese who are struggling to survive and desperately trying to save the country they love.\n\nThere\u2019s Rima, the owner of a once-grand now crumbling hotel in the country\u2019s east, a former haunt of kings, queens and presidents.\n\nToday tourism has dried up and the hotel is struggling. Rima spends her time organising food handouts for hungry neighbours.\n\n\u201cThe corruption\u2026has eaten up the Lebanon we\u2019ve known and we\u2019re all trying to save it\u201d, she tells us.\n\nHe meets Tarek, the star of Revolution TV who\u2019s live-streaming the protestors\u2019 every move for his popular YouTube channel.\n\n\u201cIt\u2019s very sad what\u2019s happening but Beirut will never die. Beirut will get sick but Beirut will survive.\u201d\n\nThere\u2019s Tala, a young DJ and part owner of Beirut\u2019s biggest nightclub. Instead of spinning discs, she\u2019s in lockdown, worried about her country\u2019s future.\n\n\u201cRight now, our country has sunk so low\u2026and it will be very, very hard to come back from that.\u201d\n\nAnd we meet unemployed Imad Awad, who doesn\u2019t have enough money to pay for heating or his wife\u2019s medicine.\n\nThe coronavirus is putting more pressure on a country already in strife. But it can\u2019t kill the revolution. As the lockdown lifts, the protestors are coming back.\n\n\u201cWe want action now. We want to see a result immediately on the streets for the people \u2013 otherwise there is no country\u201d, warns Tarek.\n\nIn a visually arresting story, we meet four Lebanese from different walks of life, all united in their desire to bring their country back from the brink.\n\n\nAbout Foreign Correspondent: \nForeign Correspondent is the prime-time international public affairs program on Australia's national broadcaster, ABC-TV. {"publishedAt": "2020-07-02T11:33:13Z", "channelId": "UCknLrEdhRCp1aegoMqRaCZg", "title": "How the Hagia Sophia became Turkey\u2019s latest political battleground | DW News", "description": "President Recep Tayyip Erdogan wants to turn Istanbul's world-famous tourist site into a mosque. He is trying to score points with Turkish voters, but his plans have encountered considerable resistance.\n\nThe Hagia Sophia is the symbol of Istanbul and Turkey's most popular tourist attraction. Every year, millions of visitors take in its gigantic brick dome and elaborate frescoes, which have earned the building UNESCO World Cultural Heritage site status.\nBut the Hagia Sophia is more than just an architectural masterpiece: It has always been a political symbol, as well. The monumental structure was built by the Byzantine Emperor Justinian in the sixth century A.D. When the Ottomans conquered Constantinople in 1453, Sultan Mehmed II immediately converted the cathedral into a mosque. The founder of the Turkish Republic, Mustafa Kemal Ataturk, utilized the church for another act with symbolic significance: In 1935 he turned the Hagia Sophia into a museum, which conveyed the message that modern Turkey was a secular country.\nNow, the current Turkish president, Recep Tayyip Erdogan, is also planning on making symbolic capital out of the building, which is situated in Istanbul's central Fatih district. For many of Erdogan's voters, who tend to have nationalist-Islamist sympathies, the Hagia Sophia symbolizes the conquest of Christian Constantinople by the Ottomans, and the superiority of the Islamic world.\nPresident Erdogan appears unfazed by objections, recently telling the Greek Orthodox community in Turkey: \"You say to us: 'Please don't turn the Hagia Sophia into a mosque.' Do you mean Turkey should bow to your will? We await the decision of the Council of State. After that, the necessary steps will be taken.\"\nErdogan's initiative is seen as an attempt to swing the Turkish electorate back behind the AKP. The majority of polls indicate that the party has lost significant support of late. Every year, millions of visitors take in its gigantic brick dome and elaborate frescoes, which have earned the building UNESCO World Cultural Heritage site status.\nBut the Hagia Sophia is more than just an architectural masterpiece: It has always been a political symbol, as well. The monumental structure was built by the Byzantine Emperor Justinian in the sixth century A.D. When the Ottomans conquered Constantinople in 1453, Sultan Mehmed II immediately converted the cathedral into a mosque. The founder of the Turkish Republic, Mustafa Kemal Ataturk, utilized the church for another act with symbolic significance: In 1935 he turned the Hagia Sophia into a museum, which conveyed the message that modern Turkey was a secular country.\nNow, the current Turkish president, Recep Tayyip Erdogan, is also planning on making symbolic capital out of the building, which is situated in Istanbul's central Fatih district. For many of Erdogan's voters, who tend to have nationalist-Islamist sympathies, the Hagia Sophia symbolizes the conquest of Christian Constantinople by the Ottomans, and the superiority of the Islamic world.\nPresident Erdogan appears unfazed by objections, recently telling the Greek Orthodox community in Turkey: \"You say to us: 'Please don't turn the Hagia Sophia into a mosque.' Do you mean Turkey should bow to your will? We await the decision of the Council of State. After that, the necessary steps will be taken.\"\nErdogan's initiative is seen as an attempt to swing the Turkish electorate back behind the AKP. The majority of polls indicate that the party has lost significant support of late. \u00f6\u011frenir.\nKe\u015fif ekibine kat\u0131lan Ke\u015fanl\u0131 ve \u00c7aylak ise beklemedikleri bir sald\u0131r\u0131yla kar\u015f\u0131 kar\u015f\u0131ya kal\u0131rlar. \u00c7atlak kollar\u0131nda \u015fehit olmak \u00fczeredir.\n\nT\u00fcrkiye'de ilk defa Genel Kurmay Ba\u015fkanl\u0131\u011f\u0131 ve Milli Savunma Bakanl\u0131\u011f\u0131 i\u015f birli\u011fi ile Ba\u015fkanl\u0131\u011f\u0131 ve Milli Savunma Bakanl\u0131\u011f\u0131 i\u015f birli\u011fi ile ger\u00e7ekle\u015ftirilen 'S\u00d6Z', bir \"\u00d6zel Kuvvet Timi'nin\" hikayesini konu al\u0131yor. \n\u00d6n haz\u0131rl\u0131klar\u0131 1 y\u0131l s\u00fcren ve \u00e7ekimleri yakla\u015f\u0131k 3 ayd\u0131r devam eden 'S\u00d6Z' de k\u0131demli \u00fcste\u011fmen ve tim komutan\u0131 Yavuz Today, we are eating our way through ADANA, one of the most famous cities for TURKISH STREET FOOD! \n\nWe eat Ci\u011fer kebab (liver kebab) for breakfast, which was cooked over charcoal. The best way to enjoy liver kebabs is to cover them in cumin powder and eat the fatty chunks. Next, we wash down the street food kebab with \u015ealgam suyu (fermented purple carrot juice), which is very similar to Turkey\u2019s pickle juices. Of course, we needed to try ADANA KEBAB in Adana, so we ordered two big plates. It was cooked to perfection over charcoal with loads of spice and was extremely JUICY! \n\nLater, we visited Kazim Bufe to try their famous Banana Milkshake. It was served super cold, sweet and jam packed with fresh bananas. To end our amazing day of eating, we wanted to try another Adana specialty, which is \u015e\u0131rdan and Mumbar (braised and stuffed sheep intestine). Although we usually do not enjoy intestines, having all kinds of Turkish spices seasoning the dishes, it tasted quite delicious!\n\nAlso in the market was a traditional cafe serving amazing k\u00fcnefe and charcoal coffee. The k\u00fcnefe was made fresh and all handmade. \n\nThanks for watching this video and we hope ADANA STREET FOOD will blow your mind! \u00f6\u011frenir.\nKe\u015fif ekibine kat\u0131lan Ke\u015fanl\u0131 ve \u00c7aylak ise beklemedikleri bir sald\u0131r\u0131yla kar\u015f\u0131 kar\u015f\u0131ya kal\u0131rlar. \u00c7atlak a\u011f\u0131r yaralan\u0131r. \u00dcstelik bir harabede s\u0131k\u0131\u015f\u0131rlar ve yard\u0131m \u00e7a\u011fr\u0131lar\u0131n\u0131 kimse duyamaz. \u00c7aylak, Ke\u015fanl\u0131'n\u0131n kollar\u0131nda \u015fehit olmak \u00fczeredir.\n\nT\u00fcrkiye'de ilk defa Genel Kurmay Ba\u015fkanl\u0131\u011f\u0131 ve Milli Savunma Bakanl\u0131\u011f\u0131 i\u015f birli\u011fi ile ba\u015far\u0131l\u0131 oyuncu Tolga Sar\u0131ta\u015f canland\u0131r\u0131rken; vatan\u0131 i\u00e7in g\u00f6z\u00fcn\u00fc k\u0131rpmadan \u00f6l\u00fcme y\u00fcr\u00fcyen bu \u00f6zel timin "2020-10-30T17:20:50Z", "channelId": "UChirEOpgFCupRAk5etXqPaA", "title": "LIVE: At Least 7 Dead After Aegean Sea Earthquake Destroys Buildings in Turkey and Greece", "description": "A powerful earthquake collapsed more than a dozen buildings in Turkey\u2019s Aegean port city of Izmir, killing at least six people, with tremors felt as far away as the commercial capital Istanbul.\n\nA seventh person died on a Greek island near the Turkish coastline.\n\nTurkey\u2019s Disaster and Emergency Management Presidency said at least 202 people had been injured. About 70 people trapped under rubble in Izmir had been rescued, state-run Anadolu Agency reported.\n\nThe epicenter of the quake, which was given a preliminary magnitude of 7.0 by the U.S. Geological Survey, was 17 kilometers (10 miles) off the coastal town of Seferihisar, Turkey\u2019s disaster management authority said. The Istanbul-based Kandilli Observatory gave it a magnitude of 6.9.\n\nGreek authorities issued a tsunami warning for the island of Samos after the earthquake, state-run ERT reported. People received a text message on their mobile phones to evacuate coastal areas. One high-school student on the island was killed and another remains unconscious after a wall collapsed on them, ERT said.\n\nGreek Prime Minster Kyriakos Mitsotakis called Turkish President Recep Tayyip Erdogan to offer his condolences for the \u201ctragic loss of life from the earthquake that struck both our countries,\u201d the Greek premier said in a Twitter post. \u201cWhatever our differences, these are times when our people need to stand together,\u201d he said.\n\nThe two countries have for weeks been involved in heated disputes over Turkish energy exploration in the eastern Mediterranean and the divided island of Cyprus.\n\nThe lira weakened as much as 1.1% to a record low of 8.3829 per dollar. Turkish oil companies Tupras and Socar said their refineries at the Aliaga peninsula, about 120 kilometers north of the epicenter, were continuing without disruption.\n\n\u201cBridges have collapsed and we were unable to enter the town,\u201d Hasim Kavuklu, a hotel worker in the Turkish tourist town of Sigacik, said by phone. \u201cThe sea first ebbed and then came back.\u201d\n\nSome vessels capsized in the marina at Seferihisar, Kavuklu said, adding there were concerns for fishing boats out at sea at the time of the quake.\n\nIstanbul Earthquake Warnings Underlined by Eastern Turkey Tremor\n\nTurkey lies in one of the world\u2019s most active seismic zones and is crossed by numerous fault lines. coastline.\n\nTurkey\u2019s Disaster and Emergency Management Presidency said at least 202 people had been injured. About 70 people trapped under rubble in Izmir had been rescued, state-run Anadolu Agency reported.\n\nThe epicenter of the quake, which was given a preliminary magnitude of 7.0 by the U.S. Geological Survey, was 17 kilometers (10 miles) off the coastal town of Seferihisar, Turkey\u2019s disaster management authority said. The Istanbul-based Kandilli Observatory gave it a magnitude of 6.9.\n\nGreek authorities issued a tsunami warning for the island of Samos after the earthquake, state-run ERT reported. People received a text message on their mobile phones to evacuate coastal areas. oyuncu Tolga Sar\u0131ta\u015f canland\u0131r\u0131rken; vatan\u0131 i\u00e7in g\u00f6z\u00fcn\u00fc k\u0131rpmadan \u00f6l\u00fcme y\u00fcr\u00fcyen bu \u00f6zel timin di\u011fer mensuplar\u0131n\u0131, Atakan Arslan, Burak Sevin\u00e7, G\u00f6rkem Sevindik, Mustafa Y\u0131ld\u0131ran, Eren Vurdem, Ayta\u00e7 \u015ea\u015fmaz, Mehmet Ali Karaku\u015f, Do\u011fukan Polat, In this video, we're giving you an overview of the European and Asian sides to give you a better sense of what each is like. And if you're trying to decide where to stay during your visit to Istanbul, we have you covered! Most tourists only visit the European side - with very good reason! - as most of the main attractions are located there. It's exciting, walkable, and you'll love the energy and hustle bustle. But seriously, you don't want to miss out on visiting the Asian side as well, which is slower paced and has a more local feel. With the support of the Lebanese diaspora around the world, generous donations from proud Lebanese ex-pats, and \"California Garden\" (www.californiagarden.com) products, (KOL W TA3ME) initiative was created to bring help for Lebanon. \"Kol w Ta3me\" initiative aims to support local businesses, small restaurants, home artisans & hard workers while feeding people in need. Supporting and boosting the economy, one small amount at a time. During this summer season, we will be visiting small businesses, supporting them with a generous amount of money which they will use to prepare food for people in need. After that, the goods will be carefully distributed for local NGOs, associations, and families around Lebanon. From Saida to Tripoli, from Antelias to the Bekaa valley, we will try to cover the entire territory. Supported by a generous donation from Fouad El Abd (California Garden) and many Lebanese residing outside Lebanon, NoGarlicNoOnions aims to distribute thousands of food portions before the end of summer. \n\nYou can join the initiative that aims to help and feed Lebanon by transferring your donations to PayPal: (rahayel@me.com) or Western Union in my name (Anthony Rahayel). Breakfast with the Fishermen. Installation of Solar Energy Lighting\n.\nKOL W TA3ME: Helping Lebanon with the Support of California Garden & the Lebanese Diaspora. With the support of the Lebanese diaspora around the world, generous donations from proud Lebanese ex-pats, and \"California Garden\" (www.californiagarden.com) products, (KOL W TA3ME) initiative was created to bring help for Lebanon. \n\n\"Kol w Ta3me\" initiative aims to support local businesses, small restaurants, home artisans & hard workers while feeding people in need. Supporting and boosting the economy, one small amount at a time. During this summer season, we will be visiting small businesses, supporting them with a generous amount of money which they will use to prepare food for people in need. After that, the goods will be carefully distributed for local NGOs, associations, and families around Lebanon. From Saida to Tripoli, from Antelias to the Bekaa valley, we will try to cover the entire territory. Supported by a generous donation from Fouad El Abd (California Garden) and many Lebanese residing outside Lebanon, NoGarlicNoOnions aims to distribute thousands of food portions before the end of summer. \n\nYou can join the initiative that aims to help and feed Lebanon by transferring your donations to PayPal: (rahayel@me.com) or Western Union in my name (Anthony Rahayel). Labneh Sandwich at 3088 Meters\n\nQurnat as Sawd\u0101\u2019 (Arabic: \u0627\u0644\u0642\u0631\u0646\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0633\u0648\u062f\u0627\u0621\u200e, Syriac: Qornet Shodo or Qornet Sod\u00e9), the Martyrs Summit, in Jabal al-Makmel is the highest point in Lebanon and the Levant, at 3,093 meters above sea level. The Secret Revealed", "description": "#Lebanon #LebanonTourism #LebaneseVillages #MadeinLebanon #\u0644\u0628\u0646\u0627\u0646\n.\nThe Best KNEFEH (Kunafa, kanafeh, kenafeh, knafeh, kunafah, kunafeh, konafa, kunafa) : Our Signature Homemade Recipe!\n.\n\u0623\u0641\u0636\u0644 \u0643\u0646\u0627\u0641\u0629: \u0648\u0635\u0641\u0629 \u0645\u0645\u064a\u0632\u0629 \u0645\u062d\u0644\u064a\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0635\u0646\u0639! \u0643\u0634\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u0633\u0631 (\u0631\u0642\u0627\u0626\u0642 \u0627\u0644\u0630\u0631\u0629 \u060c \u0641\u062a\u0627\u062a \u0627\u0644\u062e\u0628\u0632)\n.\nHomemade Knefeh recipe: our way! Probably the best out there:\n\n- 235 g butter\n- 500 g shredded mozzarella (Processed mozzarella sold in bags)\n- 400 g shredded akkawi cheese (350-400g)\n- 70g corn flakes\n- 1 pack of square bread \n- 1 cup semolina\n- 3 1/2 cups Full fat Milk \n- 4 tbsp sugar \n- 1 1/2 tsp Mastika (Mistki)\n- 2 tbsp orange blossom water\n- 2 tbsp rose water\n- Sugar Syrup (to be added on top before eating)\n.\nKnefeh\n\nKnefeh is a traditional Middle Eastern dessert made with thin noodle-like pastry, or alternatively fine semolina dough or even crushed bread crumbs, soaked in sweet, sugar-based syrup. Knefeh is typically layered with cheese or ashta (clotted cream). Some countries also add nuts.\n\nIn Lebanon, Knefeh is a a famous all-day breakfast or dessert, considered to be one of the country\u2019s most famous street foods. Lebanon\u2019s national cheesecake is a craving for all ages. The tradition wants us to eat it in bread, which our neighbors don\u2019t understand and question. The more the cheese melts, the more the Knefeh is sexy.\n\nSo many people, including Turks, think it is Turkish, but it is Arabic, but there are different varieties of Kunefe. The English language borrows the word from Levantine or Egyptian Arabic, and may employ numerous different spellings, such as kanafeh, kenafeh, knafeh, kunafah, kunafeh, konafa, kunafa, and similar variations.\n\nKnefeh is melting creamy inside, cheesy and soft, covered with a layer of sweet crispy wiry 'threads' or crumbs. The crust can be soft or crunchy, lightly sweet or soaked with an overdose of sugar. Knefeh is a dangerous piece of dessert. Enjoyed as a breakfast or after a meal in Lebanon and Middle East.\n\nOne of the most well-known preparations of kanafeh is knafeh nabulsiyeh, which originated in the Palestinian city of Nablus, and is the most representative and iconic Palestinian dessert. Knafeh nabilsiyeh uses a white-brine cheese called Nabulsi. It is prepared in a large round shallow dish, the pastry is colored with orange food coloring, and sometimes topped with crushed pistachio nuts.\n\nThere are many types of Kanafeh pastry:\n* khishnah (\u062e\u0634\u0646\u0629\u200e, rough): crust made from long thin noodle threads.\n* na'ama (\u0646\u0627\u0639\u0645\u0629\u200e, fine): semolina dough.\n* mhayara (\u0645\u062d\u064a\u0631\u0629\u200e, mixed): a mixture of khishnah and na'ama.\n* mbrwma (\u0645\u0628\u0631\u0648\u0645\u0629\u200e, twined): It is prepared with noodle.\n\nAshta Knefeh is a speciality of north Lebanon, mostly found in Tripoli, Akkar and Zgharta. When asked about Lebanese sweets, my answer is clear: north Lebanon is known for its ashta based sweets, the south is excellent at maamoul madd and cheese Knefeh. Take \u201cZnoud el Sett\u201d for instense or rolled \u201cHalawat el Jeben\u201d... I would drive all the way to Akkar for them!\n\nWhy not try a Knefeh variation. Add chocolate, Nutella, fruits... drizzle some chocolate, mango or strawberry coulis... Knefeh is great as it is but can turn into a culinary innovation: Knefeh crepe, Knefeh croissant, Knefeh burger, Knefeh cake and the list goes on and on; be creative! How do you imagine it?\n.\n#Shareyourknefeh\n.\n#knefeh #kounafa #kanafeh #kounafe #alldaybreakfast #breakfast #streetfood #lebanesestreetfood #moltencheese #meltedcheese #cheesecake #semolina #breadcrumbs #nogarlicnoonions #lebanon #middleeast #knefehsandwich #breakfastsandwich #sweettreat #sweets #lebanesesweets #middleeasternfood #saida #tripoli #tastyeats #eeeeeats #kunafa #earlymorning #riseandshine \n.\n\u201cLebnen A7la Balad Bel 3alam\u201d and I\u2019ve been trying to prove it since 2012. \u0627\u0644\u0641\u062a\u0631\u0629 10-12 \u0634\u0647\u0631 \u0648\u0642\u062f \u064a\u062a\u0623\u062e\u0631 \u0627\u0644\u0627\u0637\u0641\u0627\u0644 \u0641\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0634\u064a \u0627\u0644\u064a \u0645\u0627 \u0628\u0639\u062f \u0633\u0646 \u0633\u0646\u0629.\n\n\ud83d\udc48 \u064a\u0639\u062a\u0628\u0631 \u0627\u0644\u0637\u0641\u0644 \u0645\u062a\u0623\u062e\u0631\u0627 \u0641\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0634\u064a \u0627\u0630\u0627 \u0627\u062a\u0645 \u0627\u0644\u0637\u0641\u0644 18 \u0634\u0647\u0631 \u0648\u0644\u0645 \u064a\u0628\u062f\u0623 \u0641\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0634\u064a.\n\n\ud83d\udc48 \u0644\u0627\u0628\u062f \u0627\u0646 \u064a\u0627\u062e\u0630 \u0627\u0644\u0637\u0641\u0644 \u0641\u064a\u062a\u0627\u0645\u064a\u0646 \u062f \u0645\u0646\u0630 \u0627\u0644\u0648\u0644\u0627\u062f\u0629 \u0628\u0645\u0639\u062f\u0644 4 \u0646\u0642\u0637 \u0641\u064a\u062a\u0627\u0645\u064a\u0646 \u062f \u064a\u0648\u0645\u064a\u0627 \n\n\ud83d\udc48 \u0644\u0627\u0628\u062f \u0645\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0645\u062a\u0627\u0628\u0639\u0629 \u0645\u0639 \u0627\u0644\u0637\u0628\u064a\u0628 \u0644\u0645\u0639\u0631\u0641\u0629 \u0637\u0641\u0644.\r\n\r\n\u2705 \u0639\u0646\u0648\u0627\u0646 \u0639\u064a\u0627\u062f\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u062f\u0643\u062a\u0648\u0631 \u064a\u0648\u0633\u0641 \u0642\u0636\u0627 - With the support of the Lebanese diaspora around the world, generous donations from proud Lebanese ex-pats, and \"California Garden\" (www.californiagarden.com) products, (KOL W TA3ME) initiative was created to bring help for Lebanon.\n.\n\"Kol w Ta3me\" initiative aims to support local businesses, small restaurants, home artisans & hard workers while feeding people in need. Supporting and boosting the economy, one small amount at a time. During this summer season, we will be visiting small businesses, supporting them with a generous amount of money which they will use to prepare food for people in need. After that, the goods will be carefully distributed for local NGOs, associations, and families around Lebanon.\n.\nFrom Saida to Tripoli, from Antelias to the Bekaa valley, we will try to cover the entire territory. Karabatak\u2019\u0131n kahramanl\u0131\u011f\u0131yla Nazl\u0131 Derman\u2019\u0131n adamlar\u0131n\u0131n elinden kurtulur ama durumu a\u011f\u0131rd\u0131r.\nHaf\u0131z komutas\u0131ndaki tim ise \u00c7aylak ve Ke\u015fanl\u0131\u2019ya ula\u015fmay\u0131 ba\u015far\u0131r ama \u00e7ok fazla kan kaybeden \u00c7aylak\u2019\u0131n nabz\u0131 giderek d\u00fc\u015fmektedir. Hemen T\u00fcrkiye\u2019ye d\u00f6nmeleri gerekmektedir. Fakat bu o kadar kolay olmaz. "2020-09-11T13:00:06Z", "channelId": "UCwVIj-OqEjXNqKpItChRrMQ", "title": "How To Make Tomato Paste", "description": "Make Tomato Paste at home! In Turkish cuisine, tomato paste is one of the essential ingredients. It is easier then you might think of making it at home. With this technique, you don't have to peel tomatoes. If you are living in a hot dry climate as in some parts of Turkey, you can make your tomato paste in the sun too...\nDetailed written recipe: http://www.turkishfoodtravel.com/2020/10/04/how-to-make-tomato-paste/\nIngredients for tomato paste:\n5 kg. plum tomatoes\n4 tbsp rock salt\n2-3 tbsp olive oil\na colander\npreferable hand blender or food processor to puree the tomatoes or you can do it by hand to\nWATCH HOW TO MAKE PEPPER PASTE: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=B77CTfQ8rUM\nWash and take out the bad parts of the tomatoes if there is any. \nCut them in four. Separate them into two parts for easy handling and put it on a colander.\nSprinkle 2 tbsp rock salt on each and mix it with hand. Let it sit for about 5-6 hours. You will see a clear juice coming from the tomatoes and drain under the colander. This way it will reduce the cooking time to become a paste.\nTransfer the tomatoes to a big wide pan and begin to cook on low heat. You can stir from time to time and continue to cook for about 15 minutes until they are soft.\nUsing a strong hand blender or food processor process to tomatoes to make a puree. Now we have to strain the puree to get rid of all the seeds and the skin. Use a big colander like in the video and strain by helping with your palm or back of a measuring cup or such.\n\nCook the strained tomato puree on very low heat, stirring from time to time. It takes about 5-6 hours to become a paste. You can do this part the other day too if you don't have time or if its already a night :)\nAdd about 2 tbsp olive oil and taste the paste: it should be saltier than regular dishes since it will also help to keep the puree fresh.\nTransfer your tomato paste to a clean, boiled, and dried jar and cover the top of the tomato paste with olive oil to seal it from the air so it doesn't form a mold. In total, I got about 900gr. tomato paste from 5 kg. tomatoes. In Turkish cuisine, tomato paste is one of the essential ingredients. It is easier then you might think of making it at home. With this technique, you don't have to peel tomatoes. If you are living in a hot dry climate as in some parts of Turkey, you can make your tomato paste in the sun too...\nDetailed written recipe: http://www.turkishfoodtravel.com/2020/10/04/how-to-make-tomato-paste/\nIngredients for tomato paste:\n5 kg. plum tomatoes\n4 tbsp rock salt\n2-3 tbsp olive oil\na colander\npreferable hand blender or food processor to puree the tomatoes or you can do it by hand to\nWATCH HOW TO MAKE PEPPER PASTE: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=B77CTfQ8rUM\nWash and take out the bad parts of the tomatoes if there is any. \nCut them in four. Separate them into two parts for easy handling and put it on a colander.\nSprinkle 2 tbsp rock salt on each and mix it with hand. Let it sit for about 5-6 hours. This way it will reduce the cooking time to become a paste.\nTransfer the tomatoes to a big wide pan and begin to cook on low heat. You can stir from time to time and continue to cook for about 15 minutes until they are soft.\nUsing a strong hand blender or food processor process to tomatoes to make a puree. {"locationDescription": "Lebanon", "location": {"latitude": 33.854721, "longitude": 35.862285, "altitude": 0}}}, {"kind": "youtube#video", "etag": "LN01P0XLuB6Fxqsn4UfMGEYd7Vo", "id": "OqEab89YWQ4", "snippet": {"publishedAt": "2020-09-11T13:00:06Z", "channelId": "UCwVIj-OqEjXNqKpItChRrMQ", "title": "How To Make Tomato Paste", "description": "Make Tomato Paste at home! In Turkish cuisine, tomato paste is one of the essential ingredients. It is easier then you might think of making it at home. With this technique, you don't have to peel tomatoes. If you are living in a hot dry climate as in some parts of Turkey, you can make your tomato paste in the sun too...\nDetailed written recipe: http://www.turkishfoodtravel.com/2020/10/04/how-to-make-tomato-paste/\nIngredients for tomato paste:\n5 kg. plum tomatoes\n4 tbsp rock salt\n2-3 tbsp olive oil\na colander\npreferable hand blender or food processor to puree the tomatoes or you can do it by hand to\nWATCH HOW TO MAKE PEPPER PASTE: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=B77CTfQ8rUM\nWash and take out the bad parts of the tomatoes if there is any. \nCut them in four. Separate them into two parts for easy handling and put it on a colander.\nSprinkle 2 tbsp rock salt on each and mix it with hand. Let it sit for about 5-6 hours. You will see a clear juice coming from the tomatoes and drain under the colander. This way it will reduce the cooking time to become a paste.\nTransfer the tomatoes to a big wide pan and begin to cook on low heat. You can stir from time to time and continue to cook for about 15 minutes until they are soft.\nUsing a strong hand blender or food processor process to tomatoes to make a puree. Now we have to strain the puree to get rid of all the seeds and the skin. Use a big colander like in the video and strain by helping with your palm or back of a measuring cup or such.\n\nCook the strained tomato puree on very low heat, stirring from time to time. It takes about 5-6 hours to become a paste. You can do this part the other day too if you don't have time or if its already a night :)\nAdd about 2 tbsp olive oil and taste the paste: it should be saltier than regular dishes since it will also help to keep the puree fresh.\nTransfer your tomato paste to a clean, boiled, and dried jar and cover the top of the tomato paste with olive oil to seal it from the air so it doesn't form a mold. In total, I got about 900gr. tomato paste from 5 kg. tomatoes. In Turkish cuisine, tomato paste is one of the essential ingredients. It is easier then you might think of making it at home. With this technique, you don't have to peel tomatoes. If you are living in a hot dry climate as in some parts of Turkey, you can make your tomato paste in the sun too...\nDetailed written recipe: http://www.turkishfoodtravel.com/2020/10/04/how-to-make-tomato-paste/\nIngredients for tomato paste:\n5 kg. plum tomatoes\n4 tbsp rock salt\n2-3 tbsp olive oil\na colander\npreferable hand blender or food processor to puree the tomatoes or you can do it by hand to\nWATCH HOW TO MAKE PEPPER PASTE: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=B77CTfQ8rUM\nWash and take out the bad parts of the tomatoes if there is any. \nCut them in four. Separate them into two parts for easy handling and put it on a colander.\nSprinkle 2 tbsp rock salt on each and mix it with hand. Let it sit for about 5-6 hours. You will see a clear juice coming from the tomatoes and drain under the colander. This way it will reduce the cooking time to become a paste.\nTransfer the tomatoes to a big wide pan and begin to cook on low heat. You can stir from time to time and continue to cook for about 15 minutes until they are soft.\nUsing a strong hand blender or food processor process to tomatoes to make a puree. Now we have to strain the puree to get rid of all the seeds and the skin. Use a big colander like in the video and strain by helping with your palm or back of a measuring cup or such.\n\nCook the strained tomato puree on very low heat, stirring from time to time. It takes about 5-6 hours to become a paste. You can do this part the other day too if you don't have time or if its already a night :)\nAdd about 2 tbsp olive oil and taste the paste: it should be saltier than regular dishes since it will also help to keep the puree fresh.\nTransfer your tomato paste to a clean, boiled, and dried jar and cover the top of the tomato paste with olive oil to seal it from the air so it doesn't form a mold. In total, I got about 900gr. tomato paste from 5 kg. tomatoes. Bayilere sunulan \u00fcr\u00fcnler -zarar g\u00f6rmemi\u015fse- T\u00fcketici hukuku zaman k\u0131s\u0131tlar\u0131na ba\u011fl\u0131 kalmaks\u0131z\u0131n her zaman iade al\u0131nabiliyor. Bu anlamda, m\u00fc\u015fteri memnuniyeti \u00f6n planda tutuluyor.\n\nBagider \u00fcyesi Aktifbebek; stoktan sat\u0131\u015f yaparak sanal bayilik veren bebek sekt\u00f6r\u00fcn\u00fcn ilk ve tek firmas\u0131 olarak faaliyetini artt\u0131rak devam ediyor.\n\nBa\u015fvuru i\u00e7in : https://www.aktifbebek.com/form/bayilik-basvuru-formu"}, "defaultAudioLanguage": "tr"}, "contentDetails": Karabatak\u2019\u0131n kahramanl\u0131\u011f\u0131yla Nazl\u0131 Derman\u2019\u0131n adamlar\u0131n\u0131n elinden kurtulur ama durumu a\u011f\u0131rd\u0131r.\nHaf\u0131z komutas\u0131ndaki tim ise \u00c7aylak ve Ke\u015fanl\u0131\u2019ya ula\u015fmay\u0131 ba\u015far\u0131r ama \u00e7ok fazla kan kaybeden \u00c7aylak\u2019\u0131n nabz\u0131 giderek d\u00fc\u015fmektedir. Hemen T\u00fcrkiye\u2019ye d\u00f6nmeleri gerekmektedir. Fakat bu o kadar kolay olmaz. Yolda kar\u015f\u0131la\u015ft\u0131klar\u0131 hain pusu \u00c7aylak\u2019\u0131n ya\u015fam m\u00fccadelesini giderek zorla\u015ft\u0131r\u0131r. \u00c7aylak\u2019\u0131 hayatta tutaca\u011f\u0131na s\u00f6z veren Ke\u015fanl\u0131, bu k\u0131ska\u00e7tan kurtulmak i\u00e7in can\u0131n\u0131 bile feda etmeye haz\u0131rd\u0131r.\nDerman\u2019\u0131n pe\u015fine d\u00fc\u015fen Agah, \u00c7olak\u2019la yapt\u0131\u011f\u0131 anla\u015fmay\u0131 yerine getirmek i\u00e7in kollar\u0131 s\u0131var. Fakat \u00c7olak her zamanki gibi yine b\u00fcy\u00fck bir oyun oynayarak Agah\u2019\u0131 kar\u015f\u0131s\u0131na al\u0131r. Ama Agah\u2019\u0131n her zaman bir B plan\u0131 vard\u0131r.\n\u00c7olak giderek g\u00fc\u00e7 kaybederken Derman yava\u015f yava\u015f yerini sa\u011flamla\u015ft\u0131r\u0131r. {"publishedAt": "2020-09-15T13:00:52Z", "channelId": "UCwVIj-OqEjXNqKpItChRrMQ", "title": "Turkish Wrap \"Tantuni\" With Ground Beef & Lavash Bread Recipe", "description": "Make Turkish style meat wrap \"Tantuni\" with minced meat. It is popular street food in Istanbul and all of Turkey but the recipe known from Mersin City on the coast of the Mediterranean. I am also going to show you how to make Turkish flatbread lavash too. \nHere is the written recipe on my website: http://www.turkishfoodtravel.com/2020/09/15/turkish-wrap-tantuni-lavash/ \nTraditionally Tantuni is made from a steak or tender beef and doesn't have peppers. But in this home version, I used ground beef for making it easy and lox budget and some veggies to give extra juice and taste.\nIngredients For Tantuni, Turkish Meat wrap:\n500gr. minced meat (preferable fatty or a mix of beef and lamb if you like)\n4-5 tbsp olive oil\n1 onion\n1 sweet red pepper\n3 sweet or mild hot green peppers\n1 big ripened tomato\nIf your meat doesn't have much fat, you can add 1-2 tbsp butter\nsalt, red pepper flakes, ground red pepper, cumin (about a tsp each or as desired)\nabout 4-6 tbsp water\nFor the Lavash Flatbread:\n1 cup lukewarm water\n3-4 tbsp milk\n1 tsp sugar\n1 tsp active dry yeast\nabout 3 cups or little more flour (don't add all at once)\n1 tsp salt\na rolling pin\ngriddle or big nonstick wide pan to cook\nmore flour to dust\nFor Assembling The Wrap:\n1 red onion\n1/2 tsp salt and sumac (sumac optional)\npreferably 1/4 crisp iceberg lettuce or regular lettuce, thinly sliced\nthinly sliced tomato\nthinly sliced pickles\n\n\"Story of the Word Tantuni\"\nAccording to the story, a Yoruk (A nomadic man) boils the meat to preserve it longer, sets up his counter, and puts a stove near a school. his purpose is to roast boiled meat in oil and sell it to students. He also adds Tomato, parsley, and onion to the wrap. Students ask the man who made this food, which has no name yet, \"you hit the spoon every time and make a sound \"tan tun\" what are you selling?\" \nThis reflection sound of the spoon, the sound of \"tan tun\", inspires the man and gives the answer AS \"tantuni\".\n\nMy Social media and website\nInstagram: www.instagram.com/turkishfoodtravel\nFacebook:  https://fb.me/turkishfoodtravel\nWebsite: turkishfoodtravel.com\nDon't forget to subscribe and press the notification button: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCwVIj-OqEjXNqKpItChRrMQ?sub_confirmation=1", "thumbnails": {"default": {"url": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/0W0cRZS1tok/default.jpg", "width": 120, "height": 90}, "medium": {"url": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/0W0cRZS1tok/mqdefault.jpg", "width": 320, "height": 180}, "high": {"url": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/0W0cRZS1tok/hqdefault.jpg", "width": 480, "height": 360}, "standard": {"url": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/0W0cRZS1tok/sddefault.jpg", "width": 640, "height": 480}, "maxres": {"url": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/0W0cRZS1tok/maxresdefault.jpg", "width": 1280, "height": 720}}, "channelTitle": "Turkish Food Travel", "tags": ["turkish food", "turkish recipes", "turkish cuisine", "turkish kitchen", "turkish recipes in english", "world cuisine", "turkish food travel", "aysenur altan", "tantuni", "turkish wrap", "turkish meat wrap", "turkish street food", "istanbul food", "traditional turkish food", "Turkish stir", "tantuni recipe", "street food istanbul", "ground beef recipes", "ground beef tacos"], "categoryId": "26", "liveBroadcastContent": "none", "localized": {"title": "Turkish Wrap \"Tantuni\" With Ground Beef & Lavash Bread Recipe", "description": "Make Turkish style meat wrap \"Tantuni\" with minced meat. It is popular street food in Istanbul and all of Turkey but the recipe known from Mersin City on the coast of the Mediterranean. I am also going to show you how to make Turkish flatbread lavash too. \nHere is the written recipe on my website: http://www.turkishfoodtravel.com/2020/09/15/turkish-wrap-tantuni-lavash/ \nTraditionally Tantuni is made from a steak or tender beef and doesn't have peppers. But in this home version, I used ground beef for making it easy and lox budget and some veggies to give extra juice and taste.\nIngredients For Tantuni, Turkish Meat wrap:\n500gr. minced meat (preferable fatty or a mix of beef and lamb if you like)\n4-5 tbsp olive oil\n1 onion\n1 sweet red pepper\n3 sweet or mild hot green peppers\n1 big ripened tomato\nIf your meat doesn't have much fat, you can add 1-2 tbsp butter\nsalt, red pepper flakes, ground red pepper, cumin (about a tsp each or as desired)\nabout 4-6 tbsp water\nFor the Lavash Flatbread:\n1 cup lukewarm water\n3-4 tbsp milk\n1 tsp sugar\n1 tsp active dry yeast\nabout 3 cups or little more flour (don't add all at once)\n1 tsp salt\na rolling pin\ngriddle or big nonstick wide pan to cook\nmore flour to dust\nFor Assembling The Wrap:\n1 red onion\n1/2 tsp salt and sumac (sumac optional)\npreferably 1/4 crisp iceberg lettuce or regular lettuce, thinly sliced\nthinly sliced tomato\nthinly sliced pickles\n\n\"Story of the Word Tantuni\"\nAccording to the story, a Yoruk (A nomadic man) boils the meat to preserve it longer, sets up his counter, and puts a stove near a school. his purpose is to roast boiled meat in oil and sell it to students. He also adds Tomato, parsley, and onion to the wrap. Students ask the man who made this food, which has no name yet, \"you hit the spoon every time and make a sound \"tan tun\" what are you selling?\" \nThis reflection sound of the spoon, the sound of \"tan tun\", inspires the man and gives the answer AS \"tantuni\".\n\nMy Social media and website\nInstagram: www.instagram.com/turkishfoodtravel\nFacebook:  https://fb.me/turkishfoodtravel\nWebsite: turkishfoodtravel.com\nDon't forget to subscribe and press the notification button: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCwVIj-OqEjXNqKpItChRrMQ?sub_confirmation=1"}, "defaultAudioLanguage": "en"}, "contentDetails": {"duration": "PT12M47S", "dimension": "2d", "definition": "hd", "caption": "false", "licensedContent": true, "contentRating": {}, "projection": "rectangular"}, "statistics": {"viewCount": "31897", "likeCount": "1375", "dislikeCount": "25", "favoriteCount": "0", "commentCount": "254"}, "recordingDetails": {"locationDescription": "\u0130stanbul", "location": {"latitude": 41.0082376, "longitude": 28.9783589, "altitude": 0}}}, {"kind": "youtube#video", "etag": "Oa-Ybm8DAgg6cv3v9mrXb0fHHg4", "id": "tc_K9f0XYlc", "snippet": {"publishedAt": "2020-10-29T12:00:30Z", "channelId": "UCwVIj-OqEjXNqKpItChRrMQ", "title": "Turkish Shish Kebab Recipe | Homemade Adana Kebab", "description": "Excited to share how to make a Turkish #ShishKebab recipe that is one of the most known Turkish foods. European-Mediterranean Seismological Centre meanwhile said the quake had a preliminary magnitude of 6.9, with an epicenter 13 kilometers (8 miles)  north northeast of the Greek island of Samos.\n\nThe Bu doktor Bahar olacakt\u0131r.\nKonvoyun k\u00f6ye ula\u015ft\u0131\u011f\u0131n\u0131 \u00f6\u011frenen ata\u015fe, en sa\u011flam elemanlar\u0131ndan olu\u015fturdu\u011fu bir ekibi k\u00f6y\u00fc basmak i\u00e7in g\u00f6revlendirir. Bu bask\u0131n\u0131 \u00f6nlemek i\u00e7in Ke\u015fanl\u0131 \u00f6nderli\u011findeki Tim ter\u00f6ristlerin hi\u00e7 beklemedi\u011fi bir hamle yapacakt\u0131r. Bu esnada Yavuz ise b\u00fcy\u00fck bir tehditle y\u00fcz y\u00fcze gelmi\u015ftir. Yavuz\u2019u i\u00e7inde bulundu\u011fu tuzaktan kurtarmak i\u00e7in Tim seferber olacakt\u0131r.\nK\u00f6yde de hareketli saatler ya\u015fanmaktad\u0131r. Ter\u00f6ristlerin yard\u0131mlar yerine ula\u015fmas\u0131n diye kurdu\u011fu tuzaklar sadece Yavuz\u2019u de\u011fil, Su ve \u00c7aylak\u2019\u0131 da \u00f6l\u00fcmle burun buruna getirir.\nBahar\u2019\u0131, Derman\u2019\u0131n elinden kurtarmak i\u00e7in var\u0131n\u0131 yo\u011funu ortaya koyan Yavuz ve Tim, Derman\u2019la burun burunad\u0131r. Yavuz, Bahar\u2019\u0131 kurtarman\u0131n bedelini hayat\u0131yla \u00f6demeye haz\u0131rd\u0131r.\n\nT\u00fcrkiye'de ilk defa Genel Kurmay Ba\u015fkanl\u0131\u011f\u0131 ve Milli Savunma \u0431\u0430\u0441\u0441\u0435\u0439\u043d\n\ud83d\udc8e \u0417\u0435\u043b\u0435\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u0441\u0430\u0434 + \u0411\u0435\u0441\u0435\u0434\u043a\u0438\n\ud83d\udc8e \u0412 \u043a\u0430\u0436\u0434\u043e\u043c \u043a\u043e\u043c\u043f\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0435 \u043f\u043e 2 \u043b\u0438\u0444\u0442\u0430\n\ud83d\udc8e \u0418\u0441\u043a\u0430\u043d \u043f\u043e\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0435\u043d\n\ud83d\udc8e \u0414\u043e \u043c\u043e\u0440\u044f: 350 \u043c\n  \u0414\u043e \u0446\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0440\u0430 \u041c\u0435\u0437\u0438\u0442\u043b\u0438: 10 \u043a\u043c. \n  \u0414\u043e \u0448\u043a\u043e\u043b\u044b: 1500 \u043c.\n  \u0414\u043e \u0430\u044d\u0440\u043e\u043f\u043e\u0440\u0442\u0430: 100 \u043a\u043c. \n  \u0414\u043e \u043e\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432\u043a\u0438 \u0433\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0434\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0445 \u0430\u0432\u0442\u043e\u0431\u0443\u0441\u043e\u0432 \u0438 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0434\u0443\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0432\u044b\u0445 \u043c\u0430\u0433\u0430\u0437\u0438\u043d\u043e\u0432: 50 \u043c\n  \u0414\u043e \u0440\u044b\u043d\u043a\u0430: 200 \u043c\n\ud83d\udc8e \u041f\u043b\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0440\u043e\u0432\u043a\u0430 2+1\n\ud83d\udc8e \u0421\u043e\u0432\u043c\u0435\u0449\u0435\u043d\u043d\u0430\u044f \u043a\u0443\u0445\u043d\u044f \u0433\u043e\u0442\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0439 \u043e\u0442\u0434\u0435\u043b\u043a\u043e\u0439, \u0431\u043e\u043b\u044c\u0448\u043e\u0435 \u043a\u043e\u043b\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e
